The paper deals with subspace clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. The paper also discusses the use of sparse representations and matching pursuit algorithms, which are topics typically studied in the machine learning and signal processing communities. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves numerical optimization and computational complexity analysis, which are topics that fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively.
